{
  "texts": [
    "A multi-partite graph (also known as Kpartite graph) is a graph where the nodes can be separated into K different sets.",
    "For scene understanding tasks, this allows for a graph representation where one set of nodes represent objects and another represents relationship between objects.Multi-modal graph.",
    "A multi-modal graph is one with nodes that have features from different modalities.",
    "This approach is commonly used in VQA where the image and text modalities are mixed.",
    "Multi-modal graphs enable visual features to coexist in a graph with word embeddings."
  ]
}